Key Match Events: The LA Clippers defeated the Golden State Warriors by a final score of 112-104.
Warriors star Steph Curry exited the game with an ankle injury after playing just under 27 minutes, and did not return.
Curry had 18 points and six assists before being sidelined for the remainder of the game.
Post-Match Reflections: James Harden expressed pride in what Steph Curry has accomplished in his career, mentioning their numerous battles, including those in the Western Conference playoffs.
